{
  "stem": "4078.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean it was a Sunday afternoon, and it was a very, very nice September day.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we heard this air raid warning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we ran out to see what was going on, if anything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And absolutely nothing was going on, so of course everybody went back again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my first recollection of actually the war was when they asked for volunteers to fill sandbags.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they were making announcements on the radio.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And if you went to the cinema, you saw the newsreels.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I didn't know that there was anything particular-- at that time, I didn't know there was anything particularly bad going on with the Jews.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My father tried to get-- once the Germans had marched into Holland, my father was from Holland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Once he had heard that the Germans had marched in, he tried to get in touch with his sisters.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There was no question of making a telephone call.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We didn't have a telephone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the idea of making a phone call in those days just didn't occur.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So you wrote letters.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember we wrote frantic letters, and we never got any reply.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was quite devastating, until eventually we did get our letters returned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were all stamped with swastikas and marked gone away, unknown, address unknown.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father was very, very upset.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I didn't realize even then where they had gone or why they had gone.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We just assumed that with the bombing and the shelling that they had been bombed out of their homes or whatever.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it wasn't until around-- actually till around 1942 [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that I heard a program on the radio about the concentration camps, that people had been there and they were sending messages.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
